h translations, with a new introduction to Zayas’s entire body of stories, and restores Zayas’s author’s note and prologue, omitted from previous English-language editions. Tracing her slow but steady progress from notions of ideal love to love’s treachery, Exemplary Tales of Love and Tales of Disillusion will restore Zayas to her rightful place in modern letters.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aShort stories, Spanish. 0aSpanish literatureyClassical period, 1500-1700. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  a18th century, history, historical, novels, canon, literature, literary, lifes work, selected works, spain, spanish, gender, womens studies, feminism, feminist, female, europe, european, political, politics, equality, domestic violence, reformation, religion, belief, faith, translation, love, romance, romantic, short story, collection, tales, english major, college, university.1 aGreer, Margaret R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRhodes, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022676864940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226768670423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226768670/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles